-- Update: Advance Subscription Agreement (England and Wales)
UPDATE contract_templates SET
  preamble = 'This Advance Subscription Agreement (the "Agreement") is made on {{effective_date}} (the "Effective Date") between:

(1) {{party_a_company}}, a private company limited by shares incorporated in England and Wales (company number {{company_number}}) whose registered office is at {{party_a_address}} (the "Company"); and

(2) {{party_b_name}} of {{party_b_address}} (the "Investor").

Each a "party" and together the "parties".',
  recitals = 'A. The Company is seeking funding to support its business operations and growth.

B. The Investor wishes to advance funds to the Company on the terms of this Agreement in consideration of the right to receive shares in the Company upon the occurrence of certain conversion events.

C. The parties intend that the Subscription Amount is advanced as an advance subscription for shares, and (subject to the terms of this Agreement) will be applied in subscribing for shares in the Company on a future conversion event, rather than constituting a loan.

D. The parties acknowledge that the Investor is not receiving and has not requested any investment advice from the Company, and that nothing in this Agreement constitutes an offer of shares to the public.

E. The parties wish to record the terms and conditions upon which the Subscription Amount is paid and applied towards subscription for shares.

IT IS AGREED as follows:',
  clauses = '[{"id":"definitions","type":"standard","order":1,"title":"1. DEFINITIONS AND INTERPRETATION","content":"1.1 Definitions. In this Agreement, unless the context otherwise requires:\n\n\"Administrator\" includes an administrator appointed under Schedule B1 of the Insolvency Act 1986 and any administrative receiver, receiver, manager or similar officer.\n\n\"Advance Subscription\" means the advance subscription arrangement evidenced by this Agreement pursuant to which the Investor pays the Subscription Amount to the Company in consideration of the right to receive Subscription Shares upon a Conversion Event.\n\n\"Affiliate\" means, in relation to a person, any undertaking which is a subsidiary undertaking or parent undertaking of that person, or any subsidiary undertaking of any such parent undertaking, in each case as defined in the Companies Act 2006.\n\n\"Anti-Bribery Laws\" means the Bribery Act 2010 and any guidance issued by the Secretary of State under section 9 of the Bribery Act 2010, together with all other applicable laws and regulations relating to anti-bribery and anti-corruption.\n\n\"Applicable Law\" means all applicable laws, statutes, regulations, rules, regulatory requirements, codes of practice and guidance (having the force of law), in each case as amended, re-enacted or replaced from time to time.\n\n\"Articles\" means the Company’s articles of association as amended from time to time.\n\n\"Business Day\" means a day other than a Saturday, Sunday or public holiday in England when banks in London are open for business.\n\n\"Company Capitalisation\" means, as at the time immediately prior to the relevant Conversion Event (or such other time stated in this Agreement), the fully diluted share capital of the Company comprising:\n(a) all Shares issued and outstanding;\n(b) all Shares that are reserved or allocated for issue under any employee share option plan, growth share plan, share incentive plan or other equity incentive arrangement (whether approved or unapproved) of the Company;\n(c) all Shares that are issuable upon conversion, exercise or settlement of any Convertible Securities;\n(d) all Shares that are committed to be issued pursuant to any legally binding agreement; and\n(e) any other Shares that, in accordance with customary UK venture financing practice, the board of directors of the Company (acting in good faith) determines should be included to reflect the Company’s fully diluted capitalisation,\nbut excluding, for the avoidance of doubt, any Shares issuable on conversion of this Agreement and other substantially similar advance subscription agreements or instruments to the extent the parties have agreed in writing to exclude them to avoid double counting.\n\n\"Companies Act\" means the Companies Act 2006.\n\n\"Completion\" means, in respect of any Conversion Event, the completion of the relevant transaction giving rise to conversion and the issue and allotment of the Subscription Shares.\n\n\"Confidential Information\" means all information (in whatever form) relating to the Company or any member of its group, its or their business, assets, operations, customers, suppliers, products, services, plans, trade secrets, know-how, intellectual property, finances, forecasts, strategy, employees, directors, shareholders or affairs, that is disclosed or made available to the Investor (or its Representatives) in connection with this Agreement or the transactions contemplated by it, whether before or after the Effective Date, and whether disclosed orally, visually, in writing, by electronic means or by inspection.\n\n\"Convertible Securities\" means any instrument or security that is convertible into, exercisable for, or exchangeable for Shares, including (without limitation) options, warrants, convertible loan notes, simple agreements for future equity, advance subscription agreements and similar instruments.\n\n\"Conversion\" means the conversion of the Subscription Amount into Subscription Shares in accordance with clause 3.\n\n\"Conversion Event\" means any of: (a) a Qualifying Financing; (b) an Exit Event; (c) a Winding Up; (d) a Non-Qualifying Financing election (if applicable under clause 3.9); or (e) a Long-Stop Conversion Event (if applicable under clause 3.10).\n\n\"Conversion Price\" means the price per Subscription Share at which the Subscription Amount is applied in subscribing for Subscription Shares, calculated in accordance with clause 3.\n\n\"Conversion Shares\" means the Shares issued to the Investor upon Conversion, being the Subscription Shares.\n\n\"Data Protection Legislation\" means (as applicable and as amended from time to time):\n(a) the UK GDPR;\n(b) the Data Protection Act 2018;\n(c) the Privacy and Electronic Communications (EC Directive) Regulations 2003; and\n(d) all other applicable laws and regulatory requirements relating to the processing of Personal Data and privacy.\n\n\"Discount Rate\" means {{discount_rate}}%.\n\n\"Exit Event\" means any of the following events (whether by a single transaction or a series of related transactions):\n(a) a Sale; or\n(b) an IPO.\n\n\"Financial Promotion\" means any invitation or inducement to engage in investment activity within the meaning of section 21 of the Financial Services and Markets Act 2000.\n\n\"Financing Securities\" means, in a Qualifying Financing, the class of Shares (or other equity securities) issued and sold by the Company (other than Shares issued under employee incentive arrangements or upon conversion/exercise of existing Convertible Securities).\n\n\"FSMA\" means the Financial Services and Markets Act 2000.\n\n\"Group\" means the Company and its subsidiaries and subsidiary undertakings (if any) from time to time.\n\n\"Insolvency Event\" means any of the following in relation to the Company: (a) it is unable to pay its debts within the meaning of section 123 of the Insolvency Act 1986; (b) a moratorium is obtained under Part A1 of the Insolvency Act 1986; (c) an Administrator is appointed; (d) a receiver or administrative receiver is appointed over any material asset; (e) a winding up petition is presented (and not dismissed, withdrawn or struck out within 30 days); (f) it enters into any arrangement or composition with its creditors generally; or (g) any event occurs in any jurisdiction that has an analogous effect to the foregoing.\n\n\"IPO\" means the admission of any Shares (or other securities of the Company) to trading on any recognised investment exchange or multilateral trading facility (including, without limitation, the London Stock Exchange’s Main Market or AIM) or any other public offering that results in a listing.\n\n\"KYC Checks\" means such identity verification, anti-money laundering, counter-terrorist financing, sanctions screening and source-of-funds checks as the Company (or any bank, investor or professional adviser involved in a Qualifying Financing) may reasonably require to comply with Applicable Law and internal compliance policies.\n\n\"Long-Stop Date\" means {{long_stop_date}}.\n\n\"Non-Qualifying Financing\" means an issue of Shares (or other equity securities) by the Company for the primary purpose of raising capital where the gross cash proceeds received by the Company (excluding the amount converting under this Agreement and excluding proceeds from the conversion/exercise of other Convertible Securities) are less than the Qualifying Financing Threshold.\n\n\"Permitted Disclosures\" means disclosures of Confidential Information that are permitted under clause 7.4.\n\n\"Personal Data\" has the meaning given in the UK GDPR.\n\n\"Qualifying Financing\" means a bona fide transaction or series of related transactions in which the Company issues and sells Financing Securities for the primary purpose of raising capital, in each case on arm’s length terms, where the gross cash proceeds received by the Company (excluding any conversion under this Agreement and excluding proceeds from the conversion/exercise of existing Convertible Securities) are not less than {{qualifying_round_threshold}} (the \"Qualifying Financing Threshold\").\n\n\"Representative\" means, in relation to a party, its professional advisers, employees, officers, directors, agents, consultants, auditors, insurers, financiers and (where applicable) Affiliates.\n\n\"Sale\" means:\n(a) a sale, lease, transfer, exclusive licence or other disposition of all or substantially all of the assets or undertaking of the Company;\n(b) a merger, consolidation, scheme of arrangement or other corporate reorganisation after which the holders of the Company’s voting securities immediately prior to the transaction hold less than 50% of the voting power of the surviving or acquiring entity; or\n(c) any person (or group of persons acting in concert) acquiring beneficial ownership or control of more than 50% of the voting power of the Company.\n\n\"Shares\" means shares in the capital of the Company.\n\n\"Subscription Amount\" means {{investment_amount}}.\n\n\"Subscription Price\" has the meaning given in clause 3.2.\n\n\"Subscription Shares\" means the Shares to be issued and allotted to the Investor upon Conversion pursuant to this Agreement.\n\n\"Trade Secret\" shall have the meaning given to \"trade secret\" in regulation 2 of the Trade Secrets (Enforcement, etc.) Regulations 2018 and includes information that: (a) is secret in the sense that it is not generally known among or readily accessible to persons within the circles that normally deal with that kind of information; (b) has commercial value because it is secret; and (c) has been subject to reasonable steps under the circumstances, by the person lawfully in control of it, to keep it secret.\n\n\"UK GDPR\" has the meaning given in section 3(10) (as supplemented by section 205(4)) of the Data Protection Act 2018.\n\n\"Valuation Cap\" means {{valuation_cap}}.\n\n\"Winding Up\" means: (a) a voluntary winding up of the Company; (b) any liquidation, dissolution or winding up (other than an Exit Event); or (c) the occurrence of an Insolvency Event.\n\n1.2 Interpretation. Unless the context otherwise requires:\n(a) headings are for convenience only and do not affect interpretation;\n(b) words in the singular include the plural and vice versa;\n(c) a reference to a \"person\" includes a natural person, corporate or unincorporated body (whether or not having separate legal personality);\n(d) references to any statute or statutory provision include any subordinate legislation made under it and any amendment, re-enactment or replacement of it;\n(e) \"including\" and \"in particular\" do not limit the generality of any preceding words;\n(f) references to \"writing\" include email and other electronic communications capable of being reproduced in legible form;\n(g) any obligation not to do something includes an obligation not to permit or suffer it to be done; and\n(h) where any consent, approval or determination is required under this Agreement, it shall not be unreasonably withheld or delayed unless expressly stated otherwise."},{"id":"investment","type":"standard","order":2,"title":"2. SUBSCRIPTION; PAYMENT; NATURE OF INSTRUMENT","content":"2.1 Subscription. In consideration of payment of the Subscription Amount by the Investor to the Company, the Company agrees to apply the Subscription Amount in subscribing for and allotting Subscription Shares to the Investor upon the occurrence of a Conversion Event, all in accordance with the terms of this Agreement.\n\n2.2 Payment mechanics.\n(a) The Investor shall pay the Subscription Amount to the Company within 5 Business Days of the Effective Date (or such other date as the parties agree in writing) by electronic transfer to the following account or such other account as the Company notifies to the Investor in writing: {{bank_account_details}}.\n(b) Payment shall be made in immediately available funds, free of set-off or deduction (save to the extent required by Applicable Law).\n(c) The Company shall acknowledge receipt of the Subscription Amount in writing (email sufficient).\n\n2.3 Conditions precedent (KYC). The Company is not obliged to accept the Subscription Amount (or, if received, is not obliged to complete Conversion) until it is satisfied (acting reasonably) that it has completed any KYC Checks it considers necessary. The Investor shall promptly provide such information and documentation as the Company reasonably requests for KYC Checks.\n\n2.4 No interest; not a debt instrument.\n(a) The Subscription Amount shall not accrue interest.\n(b) The parties intend that the Subscription Amount is an advance subscription for Shares and is not a loan, debt security or deposit. Save as expressly set out in this Agreement (including clause 3.7 and clause 3.8), the Investor shall have no right to demand repayment of the Subscription Amount.\n(c) Nothing in this Agreement creates a charge, security interest or encumbrance over any asset of the Company.\n\n2.5 Use of funds. Subject to Applicable Law, the Company may use the Subscription Amount for general working capital and business purposes of the Group.\n\n2.6 No partnership or agency. Nothing in this Agreement shall create a partnership, joint venture, fiduciary relationship or agency between the parties, and neither party has authority to bind the other.\n\n2.7 Company corporate actions. The Company shall use reasonable endeavours to ensure it has the necessary authorities and approvals to perform its obligations under this Agreement, including (where required) board and shareholder authorities under the Companies Act and the Articles to allot the Subscription Shares and, where applicable, to disapply statutory pre-emption rights.\n\n2.8 No shareholder rights before Conversion.\n(a) Until Conversion, the Investor is not a shareholder of the Company and has no rights as a shareholder (including voting rights, dividend rights or rights to attend meetings) solely by virtue of this Agreement.\n(b) The Investor’s rights are limited to those expressly set out in this Agreement.\n\n2.9 Register and filings. Promptly following Completion of Conversion, the Company shall (where applicable):\n(a) update its register of members to reflect the issue and allotment of the Subscription Shares;\n(b) issue a share certificate (or, if the Company operates a paperless system, provide appropriate evidence of title) to the Investor; and\n(c) make all necessary filings at Companies House, including any return of allotment."},{"id":"conversion","type":"negotiable","order":3,"title":"3. CONVERSION EVENTS; CALCULATION; MECHANICS","content":"3.1 Automatic Conversion on Qualifying Financing. Immediately prior to (and conditional upon) Completion of a Qualifying Financing, the Subscription Amount shall automatically convert into Subscription Shares, and the Company shall allot and issue to the Investor such number of Subscription Shares as is determined under clause 3.3.\n\n3.2 Subscription Price. The price per Subscription Share on Conversion in a Qualifying Financing (the \"Subscription Price\") shall be the lower of:\n(a) the price per Share paid by investors for the Financing Securities in the Qualifying Financing multiplied by (1 − Discount Rate); and\n(b) the price per Share implied by the Valuation Cap, calculated as Valuation Cap divided by the Company Capitalisation immediately prior to Completion of the Qualifying Financing.\n\n3.3 Number of Subscription Shares. The number of Subscription Shares to be issued on Conversion following a Qualifying Financing shall be:\nSubscription Amount ÷ Subscription Price,\nrounded down to the nearest whole Share, with any fractional entitlement dealt with in accordance with clause 3.12.\n\n3.4 Class and terms of Subscription Shares on Qualifying Financing.\n(a) Unless otherwise agreed in writing between the Company and the Investor, the Subscription Shares issued on Conversion in a Qualifying Financing shall be the same class of Shares as the Financing Securities (or, if the Financing Securities are not Shares, such class of Shares as is most economically equivalent to the Financing Securities, as determined in good faith by the Company’s board).\n(b) The Subscription Shares shall be issued on the same rights and subject to the same restrictions, preferences and other terms as the Financing Securities, including (without limitation) any liquidation preference, anti-dilution protections, dividend rights, voting rights, information rights, and transfer restrictions, except that the Subscription Price and the number of Shares shall be determined in accordance with this Agreement.\n(c) If investors in the Qualifying Financing are required, as a condition to Completion, to enter into a shareholders’ agreement, investment agreement, subscription agreement, articles amendments and/or other ancillary documents, the Investor shall (subject to clause 3.4(d)) enter into the same documents on substantially the same terms, provided that such documents shall not impose on the Investor any obligation to provide further funding (other than in respect of any pro rata participation elected under clause 4.6), any personal guarantee, or any non-compete or other restriction that is materially more onerous than that imposed on other investors of the same class.\n(d) The Investor’s obligation to execute ancillary documents is conditional upon the Investor being afforded a reasonable opportunity to review them in advance. The Company shall use reasonable endeavours to provide such documents to the Investor not less than 5 Business Days before Completion of the Qualifying Financing (or such shorter period as is reasonable in the circumstances).\n\n3.5 Notice of Conversion. The Company shall notify the Investor in writing as soon as reasonably practicable upon becoming aware of a likely Conversion Event and, in any event:\n(a) for a Qualifying Financing, not less than 5 Business Days prior to Completion (where practicable);\n(b) for an Exit Event, promptly after the board approves a binding term sheet or transaction document for the Exit Event (where applicable);\n(c) for a Winding Up, promptly upon the Company becoming aware of the relevant event.\n\n3.6 Conversion or settlement on Exit Event.\n(a) If an Exit Event occurs prior to Conversion on a Qualifying Financing, then (subject to clause 3.6(d)) the Investor may elect by notice to the Company (an \"Exit Election Notice\") to receive either:\n(i) a cash amount equal to the Subscription Amount (the \"Cash-Out Amount\"); or\n(ii) Conversion into Shares immediately prior to Completion of the Exit Event.\n(b) If the Investor elects Conversion under clause 3.6(a)(ii), the Conversion Price shall be the price per Share implied by the Valuation Cap, calculated as Valuation Cap divided by the Company Capitalisation immediately prior to Completion of the Exit Event (or, if the Exit Event consideration is not solely cash, such price per Share as determined in good faith by the board to reflect the total consideration).\n(c) If the Investor elects cash under clause 3.6(a)(i), the Cash-Out Amount shall be paid at Completion of the Exit Event from the proceeds otherwise payable to the Company, subject to applicable insolvency law and any contractual waterfall applicable to the transaction.\n(d) If the Company reasonably determines that an election under clause 3.6(a)(i) would adversely affect Completion of the Exit Event (including because the buyer requires all investors to roll into equity), the Company may require that the Investor take Conversion under clause 3.6(a)(ii) provided the Investor is treated no less favourably (in economic terms) than other investors holding substantially similar instruments.\n(e) If the Investor does not deliver an Exit Election Notice at least 2 Business Days prior to Completion of the Exit Event (or such other deadline as the Company reasonably specifies), the Investor shall be deemed to have elected Conversion under clause 3.6(a)(ii).\n\n3.7 Winding Up. If a Winding Up occurs before Conversion, the Company shall, subject to Applicable Law and the rights of preferential creditors, pay to the Investor an amount equal to the Subscription Amount in priority to any distribution to holders of Shares, but behind:\n(a) preferential creditors (including employees and HMRC where applicable);\n(b) secured creditors to the extent of their security; and\n(c) any costs and expenses of the insolvency or winding up.\n\n3.8 Non-Qualifying Financing (optional investor election).\n(a) If a Non-Qualifying Financing occurs prior to a Qualifying Financing, the Company shall notify the Investor and provide reasonable details of the proposed financing.\n(b) The Investor may elect by notice in writing to the Company (served prior to Completion of the Non-Qualifying Financing) either:\n(i) to convert the Subscription Amount at the lower of (A) the price per Share in that financing multiplied by (1 − Discount Rate) and (B) the price implied by the Valuation Cap; or\n(ii) to continue on the terms of this Agreement without converting.\n(c) If the Investor does not respond within the period specified by the Company (being not less than 5 Business Days where practicable), the Investor shall be deemed to have elected clause 3.8(b)(ii).\n\n3.9 Long-Stop Conversion / repayment.\n(a) If no Conversion Event has occurred on or before the Long-Stop Date, then (subject to clause 3.9(d)) the Investor may elect by notice to the Company either:\n(i) Conversion into ordinary shares of the Company (or such other class as the parties agree) at a Conversion Price equal to the price implied by the Valuation Cap; or\n(ii) repayment of the Subscription Amount.\n(b) Any election under clause 3.9(a) must be made within 30 days after the Long-Stop Date.\n(c) Repayment (if elected) shall be made within 30 Business Days of the Company receiving the Investor’s notice, subject to Applicable Law (including directors’ duties, insolvency considerations and the Companies Act rules on distributions).\n(d) The Company may satisfy an election under clause 3.9(a)(i) by procuring that the Investor is issued Shares under the Articles and Companies Act authorities then in place; if further corporate approvals are required, the Company shall use reasonable endeavours to obtain them.\n\n3.10 Most Favoured Nation (MFN).\n(a) If, prior to Conversion, the Company enters into any other advance subscription agreement, SAFE, convertible loan note, or similar instrument on terms more favourable to the investor in that instrument than the economic terms in this Agreement (taken as a whole), the Company shall notify the Investor.\n(b) The Investor may elect, by notice to the Company within 20 Business Days of receipt of such notice, to amend this Agreement so that it reflects the more favourable economic terms (including, without limitation, a higher discount, a lower valuation cap, or more favourable conversion mechanics), but excluding any terms relating to investor governance rights that are expressly personal to that investor.\n(c) The Company shall provide reasonable evidence of the relevant terms (redacted for confidentiality if necessary).\n\n3.11 No double counting; adjustments. The Company and the Investor shall act in good faith to avoid any double counting or circularity in calculating the Company Capitalisation and the Conversion Price where multiple convertible instruments convert at the same financing, and may make reasonable adjustments consistent with market practice.\n\n3.12 Fractions; rounding. No fractional Shares shall be issued. Any fractional entitlement shall be rounded down to the nearest whole Share and the Company shall either (at its option):\n(a) pay the Investor the cash value of the fraction based on the Conversion Price; or\n(b) issue one additional Share to the Investor in lieu of the fraction,\nprovided that the method is applied consistently to holders of similar instruments converting at the same time.\n\n3.13 Termination. This Agreement shall terminate automatically on the earliest of:\n(a) Completion of Conversion and issue of all Subscription Shares due under this Agreement;\n(b) repayment of the Subscription Amount under clause 3.9(a)(ii);\n(c) payment to the Investor under clause 3.7; or\n(d) written agreement of the parties.\n\n3.14 Survival. Termination shall not affect any accrued rights or obligations, nor any clause that is expressly or by implication intended to survive (including clauses 7, 8, 9, 10 and 12)."},{"id":"valuation_cap_discount","type":"negotiable","order":4,"title":"4. VALUATION CAP; DISCOUNT; NO MOST-FAVOURED TAX TREATMENT","content":"4.1 Valuation Cap. The parties agree that the Valuation Cap is intended to protect the Investor from excessive valuation uplift prior to Conversion and shall be applied strictly in accordance with clause 3.\n\n4.2 Discount Rate. The Discount Rate shall apply only where clause 3 provides for conversion by reference to a discounted price per Share.\n\n4.3 No representations as to tax relief. The Company makes no representation, warranty or undertaking that the Subscription Amount or any Subscription Shares will qualify for any particular tax treatment or relief (including under the Enterprise Investment Scheme (EIS) or Seed Enterprise Investment Scheme (SEIS)), and the Investor acknowledges that tax relief depends on statutory conditions and the Investor’s circumstances.\n\n4.4 Optional: advance assurance.\n(a) If the parties agree that the Company will seek advance assurance for EIS/SEIS, the parties may set out the agreed position here: {{eis_seis_position}}.\n(b) Any such steps shall be on a reasonable endeavours basis only and the Company shall not be liable if relief is not available."},{"id":"investor_rights","type":"optional","order":5,"title":"5. INVESTOR RIGHTS (INFORMATION; PRO RATA; OBSERVER) — OPTIONAL","content":"5.1 Information rights (pre-Conversion). From the Effective Date until termination of this Agreement, and subject to clause 5.5, the Company shall provide the Investor with:\n(a) within 120 days after each financial year end, unaudited annual accounts of the Company (or, if available, audited accounts);\n(b) within 45 days after each quarter end, management accounts (if prepared in the ordinary course);\n(c) prompt written notice of any proposed Qualifying Financing, Non-Qualifying Financing, Exit Event or Winding Up; and\n(d) such other information as the Company reasonably determines to provide to investors holding substantially similar instruments, provided that the Company is not obliged to provide information that would be materially commercially harmful to disclose.\n\n5.2 Inspection rights. Upon reasonable notice and during normal business hours, the Investor may request one meeting per calendar year with a director or senior officer of the Company to discuss the Company’s performance and prospects, provided that the Company may decline a request where it reasonably considers it would be unduly burdensome or would require disclosure of Confidential Information that cannot appropriately be shared.\n\n5.3 No control. The Investor acknowledges that any information rights do not confer any right to direct the Company’s management or operations.\n\n5.4 Notice of Conversion documents. The Company shall provide the Investor with reasonable details of the calculation of the Conversion Price and number of Subscription Shares.\n\n5.5 Confidentiality condition. The Company’s obligations under this clause 5 are conditional upon the Investor complying with clause 7 (Confidentiality).\n\n5.6 Optional — pro rata participation right.\n(a) If this Agreement converts in a Qualifying Financing, the Investor shall have the right (but not the obligation) to subscribe for additional Financing Securities in that Qualifying Financing to maintain the Investor’s percentage ownership of the Company on an as-converted basis, calculated immediately prior to Completion of the Qualifying Financing.\n(b) The Investor must exercise the right by written notice within the period specified by the Company (being not less than 5 Business Days where practicable) and shall subscribe on the same terms (including price) as other investors in the Qualifying Financing.\n(c) This right shall be subject to any allocation, oversubscription, regulatory constraints, and any limitations imposed by the lead investor or the Company’s board acting reasonably.\n\n5.7 Optional — board observer. Subject to the board’s consent and the Company’s confidentiality policies, the Company may permit the Investor to appoint a non-voting observer to attend board meetings, provided that:\n(a) the Company may exclude the observer from any meeting or part of a meeting where conflicts of interest arise or where sensitive matters are discussed (including employee matters, litigation, or negotiations);\n(b) the observer shall owe confidentiality obligations equivalent to those in clause 7; and\n(c) the observer shall not be a director and shall not have director duties.\n\n5.8 No other rights. Except as expressly set out in this Agreement, the Investor has no rights to participate in future fundraisings or to receive information."},{"id":"company_representations","type":"standard","order":6,"title":"6. COMPANY REPRESENTATIONS AND WARRANTIES","content":"6.1 General. The Company represents and warrants to the Investor as at the Effective Date and (if Conversion occurs) as at Completion of Conversion that:\n\n6.2 Incorporation and capacity.\n(a) The Company is duly incorporated and validly existing under the laws of England and Wales.\n(b) The Company has the power and authority to own its assets and carry on its business substantially as conducted at the Effective Date.\n\n6.3 Authority and enforceability.\n(a) The Company has taken (or will take prior to allotting Subscription Shares) all necessary corporate actions to authorise the execution, delivery and performance of this Agreement.\n(b) This Agreement constitutes valid and binding obligations of the Company enforceable against it in accordance with its terms, subject to applicable insolvency laws and equitable principles.\n\n6.4 No conflict. The execution, delivery and performance of this Agreement by the Company does not and will not:\n(a) contravene the Articles;\n(b) breach any Applicable Law;\n(c) result in a default under, or give any person a right to terminate, amend or accelerate, any material contract to which the Company is a party; or\n(d) create any encumbrance over the Company’s assets.\n\n6.5 Capital structure.\n(a) The Company has, and will maintain, an accurate register of members in accordance with the Companies Act.\n(b) The Company will provide, on request, a summary capitalisation table as at the Effective Date (which may be subject to customary confidentiality limitations).\n\n6.6 Valid allotment on Conversion. Upon Conversion and subject to the Company having the necessary Companies Act authorities in place at the relevant time:\n(a) the Subscription Shares shall be duly allotted and issued;\n(b) the Subscription Shares shall be fully paid; and\n(c) the Subscription Shares shall rank pari passu in all respects with the other Shares of the same class then in issue (save as may be agreed in the Qualifying Financing documents).\n\n6.7 Litigation and insolvency (to the Company’s knowledge).\n(a) No litigation, arbitration, prosecution or regulatory investigation is pending or threatened against the Company that would reasonably be expected to have a material adverse effect on the Company.\n(b) The Company is not subject to any Insolvency Event and no steps have been taken to initiate one.\n\n6.8 Compliance.\n(a) The Company has in place policies and procedures it reasonably considers appropriate for its size and nature of business to prevent bribery and corruption.\n(b) The Company has not been convicted of an offence under the Bribery Act 2010 in the last 6 years.\n\n6.9 Data protection (limited). The Company will process any Personal Data received from the Investor in accordance with clause 9 and the Data Protection Legislation.\n\n6.10 No financial promotion to the public. The Company has not taken any action that would constitute an offer of securities to the public in breach of Applicable Law in connection with this Agreement.\n\n6.11 Disclosure. The representations and warranties in this clause 6 are given subject to any matters fairly disclosed in writing by the Company to the Investor on or before the Effective Date: {{disclosure_letter_reference}}."},{"id":"investor_representations","type":"standard","order":7,"title":"7. INVESTOR REPRESENTATIONS AND WARRANTIES","content":"7.1 General. The Investor represents and warrants to the Company as at the Effective Date and (if Conversion occurs) as at Completion of Conversion that:\n\n7.2 Capacity and authority.\n(a) The Investor has full capacity, power and authority to enter into this Agreement and to perform its obligations.\n(b) Where the Investor is not an individual, the Investor is duly constituted and validly existing under the laws of its jurisdiction of incorporation/formation and has taken all necessary action to authorise execution and delivery of this Agreement.\n\n7.3 Investor status; financial promotion.\n(a) The Investor is a person to whom an invitation or inducement to engage in investment activity may lawfully be communicated without an approved Financial Promotion under FSMA, including because the Investor is an investment professional, high net worth entity/individual, sophisticated investor, or otherwise falls within an applicable exemption in the Financial Services and Markets Act 2000 (Financial Promotion) Order 2005.\n(b) The Investor is acquiring the rights under this Agreement as principal for its own account (and not as nominee for any other person) unless the Company has agreed otherwise in writing.\n\n7.4 No reliance; independent advice. The Investor acknowledges and agrees that:\n(a) the Investor has had the opportunity to take independent legal, tax and financial advice;\n(b) the Company has not provided investment advice and is not acting as the Investor’s adviser or fiduciary; and\n(c) the Investor has relied solely on its own assessment of the Company and the terms of this Agreement.\n\n7.5 Investment risk. The Investor understands that investment in early-stage companies involves a high degree of risk, the investment is illiquid, and the Investor may lose the entire Subscription Amount.\n\n7.6 Lawful funds; AML; sanctions.\n(a) The Subscription Amount is derived from legitimate sources and is not the proceeds of criminal conduct.\n(b) The Investor will provide information reasonably requested for KYC Checks.\n(c) The Investor is not, and is not owned or controlled by, any person that is the subject of sanctions administered or enforced by the UK or (where relevant to a transaction) the UN, EU or US.\n\n7.7 No improper conduct. The Investor has not offered, promised, given, requested or accepted (and will not offer, promise, give, request or accept) any financial or other advantage in breach of Anti-Bribery Laws in connection with this Agreement.\n\n7.8 Confidentiality. The Investor will comply with clause 8 (Confidentiality and Trade Secrets).\n\n7.9 No public distribution. The Investor is not acquiring this Agreement with a view to selling, distributing or otherwise transferring it in circumstances that would breach Applicable Law (including FSMA).\n\n7.10 Tax. The Investor is solely responsible for its own tax affairs and any taxes arising in connection with this Agreement or any Subscription Shares.\n\n7.11 Accuracy of information. All information provided by the Investor to the Company in connection with this Agreement (including for KYC Checks) is, to the Investor’s knowledge, true, complete and not misleading."},{"id":"confidentiality","type":"standard","order":8,"title":"8. CONFIDENTIALITY; TRADE SECRETS","content":"8.1 Confidentiality obligation. The Investor shall (and shall procure that its Representatives shall):\n(a) keep Confidential Information strictly confidential;\n(b) use Confidential Information solely for the purpose of evaluating, holding and enforcing its rights under this Agreement; and\n(c) not disclose Confidential Information to any person except as permitted under clause 8.4.\n\n8.2 Trade secrets. The parties acknowledge that certain Confidential Information may constitute Trade Secrets and that unauthorised use or disclosure may cause significant harm. The Investor shall implement reasonable measures to protect Trade Secrets and Confidential Information, including (as appropriate) access controls, password protection and need-to-know restrictions.\n\n8.3 Exclusions. Confidential Information does not include information that the Investor can demonstrate:\n(a) is or becomes generally available to the public other than through breach of this Agreement;\n(b) was lawfully in the Investor’s possession before disclosure by the Company;\n(c) is independently developed by the Investor without use of or reference to the Company’s Confidential Information; or\n(d) is lawfully obtained from a third party who is not under an obligation of confidentiality.\n\n8.4 Permitted Disclosures. The Investor may disclose Confidential Information:\n(a) to its Representatives who have a need to know for the permitted purpose and who are bound by confidentiality obligations no less protective than those in this Agreement;\n(b) as required by Applicable Law, court order, or any regulatory or tax authority, provided that (to the extent legally permitted) the Investor gives the Company prompt written notice and reasonably cooperates (at the Company’s cost) with any lawful attempt by the Company to resist or limit the disclosure;\n(c) with the Company’s prior written consent;\n(d) to the extent necessary to enforce this Agreement or in connection with a bona fide dispute, provided that the Investor uses reasonable endeavours to seek confidential treatment.\n\n8.5 Announcements. Neither party shall make any public announcement regarding this Agreement or the Subscription Amount without the prior written consent of the other, except as required by Applicable Law.\n\n8.6 Return or destruction. Upon the Company’s written request, the Investor shall promptly return or destroy Confidential Information in its possession or control, save that the Investor may retain copies to the extent required by Applicable Law or bona fide internal compliance policies, provided such retained information remains subject to this clause 8.\n\n8.7 Duration. The obligations in this clause 8 shall apply from the Effective Date and continue for a period of 5 years after termination of this Agreement, except that obligations relating to Trade Secrets shall continue for so long as the relevant information remains a Trade Secret.\n\n8.8 Remedies. The Investor acknowledges that damages alone may be an inadequate remedy for breach of this clause 8 and that the Company may seek injunctive relief or other equitable remedies. This is without prejudice to any other rights or remedies available.\n\n8.9 No licence. Nothing in this Agreement grants the Investor any licence or other rights in relation to any intellectual property or Confidential Information of the Company, except the limited right to use Confidential Information for the permitted purpose."},{"id":"compliance","type":"standard","order":9,"title":"9. COMPLIANCE (ANTI-BRIBERY; MODERN SLAVERY; SANCTIONS; TAX EVASION)","content":"9.1 Anti-bribery and corruption.\n(a) Each party shall comply with Anti-Bribery Laws.\n(b) Neither party shall (and each shall procure that its Representatives shall not) engage in any activity, practice or conduct that would constitute an offence under sections 1, 2 or 6 of the Bribery Act 2010.\n(c) The Company shall maintain (and the Investor shall, where applicable, maintain) such policies and procedures as are reasonably appropriate to prevent bribery, taking account of the nature, scale and complexity of its activities.\n\n9.2 Modern slavery (where applicable).\n(a) Where the Company is required under section 54 of the Modern Slavery Act 2015 to prepare a slavery and human trafficking statement, it shall (on request) provide the Investor with the then-current published statement or a link to it.\n(b) Each party shall not knowingly engage in any activity that would constitute an offence under sections 1, 2 or 4 of the Modern Slavery Act 2015.\n\n9.3 Sanctions. Each party represents that it is not a sanctioned person and shall not use any funds or perform any obligations under this Agreement in a manner that would breach Applicable Law relating to sanctions.\n\n9.4 Criminal facilitation of tax evasion. Each party shall not engage in any conduct which would constitute a criminal offence under Parts 3 and 3A of the Criminal Finances Act 2017 and shall maintain reasonable prevention procedures where applicable.\n\n9.5 General compliance. Each party shall promptly notify the other if it becomes aware of any matter that would reasonably be expected to cause a breach of this clause 9.\n\n9.6 Termination right (optional). Where a party materially breaches clause 9 and fails to remedy that breach within 30 days of written notice, the non-breaching party may terminate this Agreement, provided that termination shall be without prejudice to any accrued rights and shall not affect clause 8, clause 9, clause 10 and clause 12."},{"id":"data_protection","type":"standard","order":10,"title":"10. DATA PROTECTION","content":"10.1 Scope. This clause 10 applies to any Personal Data exchanged between the parties in connection with this Agreement (including names, contact details, identification documents and beneficial ownership information).\n\n10.2 Independent controllers. Each party acknowledges that, in respect of Personal Data processed under or in connection with this Agreement, the parties act as independent controllers (and not as joint controllers), unless otherwise agreed in writing.\n\n10.3 Lawful basis and purposes.\n(a) Each party shall process Personal Data lawfully, fairly and transparently and in accordance with the Data Protection Legislation.\n(b) The Company may process the Investor’s Personal Data for purposes including: (i) performing this Agreement; (ii) maintaining statutory registers and corporate records; (iii) complying with KYC Checks and legal obligations; (iv) communicating with the Investor; and (v) managing corporate actions (including Conversion Events).\n(c) The Investor may process Personal Data of Company personnel for purposes including: (i) performing this Agreement; (ii) compliance and audit; and (iii) internal governance and record keeping.\n\n10.4 Data security. Each party shall implement appropriate technical and organisational measures to protect Personal Data against unauthorised or unlawful processing and against accidental loss, destruction or damage.\n\n10.5 Data sharing and recipients. The Company may disclose Personal Data to:\n(a) its professional advisers, auditors and insurers;\n(b) regulators, tax authorities and law enforcement (where required);\n(c) banks, payment service providers and KYC providers;\n(d) investors and potential investors participating in a financing (where reasonably necessary), subject to appropriate confidentiality obligations;\n(e) the Company’s registrars or corporate service providers.\n\n10.6 International transfers. If either party transfers Personal Data outside the UK to a jurisdiction not recognised by the UK as providing an adequate level of protection, it shall ensure appropriate safeguards are in place in accordance with the Data Protection Legislation (for example, the UK International Data Transfer Agreement or the UK Addendum to the EU Standard Contractual Clauses, as applicable).\n\n10.7 Data retention. Each party shall retain Personal Data only for as long as necessary for the purposes for which it is processed, including compliance with legal, regulatory, accounting or reporting requirements.\n\n10.8 Data subject rights. Each party shall, to the extent applicable, respond to requests from data subjects to exercise their rights under the Data Protection Legislation. Where a request relates to processing by the other party, the receiving party shall promptly notify the other party where appropriate.\n\n10.9 No requirement to process special category data. The parties do not intend to exchange special category data (as defined in the UK GDPR). If special category data is processed, the parties shall agree appropriate additional safeguards.\n\n10.10 Privacy notices. Each party shall ensure it provides appropriate privacy information to individuals whose Personal Data it discloses to the other party.\n\n10.11 Liability. This clause 10 does not limit or exclude either party’s liability for breach of the Data Protection Legislation where such liability cannot be limited or excluded by Applicable Law."},{"id":"transfer_and_assignment","type":"negotiable","order":11,"title":"11. TRANSFER; ASSIGNMENT; DEALINGS","content":"11.1 No transfer by the Company. The Company may not assign, transfer, charge, declare a trust over or otherwise deal with any of its rights or obligations under this Agreement without the Investor’s prior written consent (not to be unreasonably withheld or delayed), except that the Company may transfer its rights and obligations to a successor entity in an Exit Event provided that successor assumes the Company’s obligations.\n\n11.2 Restrictions on Investor transfer. The Investor may not assign, transfer, charge, declare a trust over or otherwise deal with this Agreement or any of its rights under it without the prior written consent of the Company, except for a Permitted Transfer under clause 11.3.\n\n11.3 Permitted Transfers. The Investor may transfer this Agreement without Company consent:\n(a) to an Affiliate of the Investor;\n(b) to a nominee or custodian acting on behalf of the Investor (provided the Investor remains liable for the nominee/custodian’s acts and omissions);\n(c) in the case of an individual Investor, to a spouse/civil partner or to a trust or vehicle for estate planning purposes, or to personal representatives on death;\n(d) with the prior written consent of the Company not to be unreasonably withheld or delayed.\n\n11.4 Conditions to transfer. Any transfer (including a Permitted Transfer) is conditional upon:\n(a) the transferee executing a deed of adherence or other document reasonably required by the Company agreeing to be bound by the terms of this Agreement as if it were the original Investor;\n(b) the Investor and transferee complying with Applicable Law (including FSMA restrictions);\n(c) completion of any KYC Checks required by the Company; and\n(d) the Investor paying the Company’s reasonable costs of processing the transfer (if any), notified in advance.\n\n11.5 No partial transfers. The Investor may not transfer part only of its rights under this Agreement unless the Company agrees in writing.\n\n11.6 No listing. The parties agree that the rights under this Agreement are not intended to be listed or traded on any market.\n\n11.7 Successors. Subject to this clause 11, this Agreement shall be binding upon and inure to the benefit of the parties and their respective permitted successors and assigns."},{"id":"costs_and_tax","type":"standard","order":12,"title":"12. COSTS; TAX; WITHHOLDING; RECORDS","content":"12.1 Costs and expenses. Except as expressly stated otherwise in this Agreement, each party shall bear its own costs and expenses in connection with the negotiation, preparation, execution and performance of this Agreement.\n\n12.2 Taxes.\n(a) The Investor is responsible for any tax payable by it arising out of or in connection with this Agreement or the issue, acquisition, holding or disposal of Subscription Shares.\n(b) The Company is responsible for any taxes for which it is liable arising out of the issue and allotment of Subscription Shares (subject to Applicable Law).\n\n12.3 Withholding. If any deduction or withholding is required by Applicable Law to be made from any payment under this Agreement, the payer shall make such deduction or withholding and shall pay the net amount to the payee. The payer shall provide the payee with evidence reasonably requested of the deduction or withholding and payment to the relevant authority.\n\n12.4 Stamp taxes. If any stamp duty or stamp duty reserve tax becomes payable in connection with the transfer of this Agreement or the Subscription Shares, the parties shall comply with Applicable Law and the party liable under law shall pay such tax.\n\n12.5 Records. The Company shall maintain accurate records relating to this Agreement, including receipt of the Subscription Amount and, upon Conversion, the issue and allotment of Subscription Shares, in each case in accordance with Applicable Law.\n\n12.6 Further assurance. Each party shall, at its own cost, do and execute (or procure the doing and execution of) all such acts, documents and things as the other party may reasonably require to give effect to this Agreement and the transactions contemplated by it."},{"id":"miscellaneous","type":"standard","order":13,"title":"13. GENERAL PROVISIONS","content":"13.1 Notices.\n(a) Any notice or other communication given under or in connection with this Agreement shall be in writing and shall be:\n(i) delivered by hand;\n(ii) sent by pre-paid first-class post or other next working day delivery service; or\n(iii) sent by email.\n(b) Notices shall be sent to the addresses and emails set out in the preamble (or such other address/email as notified in accordance with this clause).\n(c) Deemed receipt:\n(i) if delivered by hand, at the time the notice is left at the proper address;\n(ii) if posted, at 9.00 am on the second Business Day after posting;\n(iii) if emailed, at the time of transmission provided no delivery failure notice is received, except that if sent outside 9.00 am–5.30 pm on a Business Day, receipt is deemed at 9.00 am on the next Business Day.\n(d) This clause does not apply to service of proceedings.\n\n13.2 Amendments and waivers.\n(a) No variation of this Agreement shall be effective unless in writing and signed by or on behalf of each party.\n(b) A waiver is effective only if in writing and applies only to the circumstances for which it is given.\n(c) A failure or delay to exercise any right or remedy does not constitute a waiver.\n\n13.3 Severance. If any provision (or part provision) of this Agreement is or becomes invalid, illegal or unenforceable, it shall be deemed modified to the minimum extent necessary to make it valid, legal and enforceable. If such modification is not possible, the provision shall be deemed deleted. Any modification or deletion shall not affect the validity and enforceability of the rest of this Agreement.\n\n13.4 Entire agreement.\n(a) This Agreement constitutes the entire agreement between the parties and supersedes all previous agreements, arrangements and understandings between them relating to its subject matter.\n(b) Each party acknowledges that it does not rely on, and shall have no remedies in respect of, any statement, representation, assurance or warranty not set out in this Agreement (subject to fraud).\n\n13.5 Third party rights. Unless expressly stated otherwise, a person who is not a party to this Agreement shall not have any rights to enforce any term of this Agreement under the Contracts (Rights of Third Parties) Act 1999.\n\n13.6 Counterparts. This Agreement may be executed in any number of counterparts, each of which when executed and delivered shall constitute a duplicate original, but all the counterparts shall together constitute the one agreement.\n\n13.7 Electronic signatures. The parties agree that this Agreement may be executed electronically and that electronic signatures shall be admissible and effective as evidence of execution in accordance with the Electronic Communications Act 2000 and applicable law.\n\n13.8 Governing law. This Agreement and any dispute or claim (including non-contractual disputes or claims) arising out of or in connection with it or its subject matter shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of England and Wales.\n\n13.9 Jurisdiction. The parties irrevocably agree that the courts of England and Wales shall have exclusive jurisdiction to settle any dispute or claim (including non-contractual disputes or claims) arising out of or in connection with this Agreement.\n\n13.10 IR35/off-payroll working rules; status.\n(a) The parties acknowledge that this Agreement relates to an investment/advance subscription and does not involve the provision of services by the Investor to the Company.\n(b) Nothing in this Agreement creates an employment, worker, agency or contractor relationship between the Investor and the Company.\n(c) The parties agree that the off-payroll working rules (commonly referred to as IR35) are not intended to apply to the arrangements contemplated by this Agreement. If, notwithstanding the parties’ intention, any authority asserts that the arrangements constitute the provision of services, the parties shall cooperate in good faith to address compliance, but nothing in this clause obliges either party to accept any re-characterisation of the relationship.\n\n13.11 Rights cumulative. The rights and remedies provided under this Agreement are cumulative and not exclusive of any rights and remedies provided by law.\n\n13.12 No assignment except as permitted. Except as permitted under clause 11, neither party may assign or transfer any of its rights or obligations under this Agreement.\n\n13.13 Time. Where this Agreement specifies a period of days, the period shall be calculated by excluding the day on which the relevant event occurs and including the last day of the period, and if the last day is not a Business Day the period shall extend to the next Business Day.\n\n13.14 Interpretation of investor protections. The parties agree that clause 5 (Investor Rights) is optional and may be deleted in whole or in part without affecting the core economic terms of clauses 2 to 4.\n\n13.15 Further documentation. The parties shall act reasonably and in good faith in connection with the preparation and execution of any ancillary documentation required to implement a Conversion Event, provided that such documentation is consistent with this Agreement and customary UK venture financing practice."}]'::jsonb,
  signature_block = 'IN WITNESS WHEREOF, the parties have executed this Agreement on the date(s) set out below.

